<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1359,1674]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1467,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gupta &amp; Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Sharma &amp; Naqvi" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[344,625,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Euscelinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="namkumensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[344,625,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Euscelinus namkumensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,764,1467,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,764,1467,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the malar space equal to basal width of mandible, and also varies in wing venation. Based on the original publication the species is reared from “Lac Stick, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saalmuller" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,374,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eublemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">
<emphasis box="[151,374,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Eublemma amabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” however this host information is probably wrong. The host should be a coleopterous larva associated with the host plant of the lac insect. The correction to the species epithet is made as it follows the gender of the generic name. It is synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood 1882" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1882" box="[661,1003,1611,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Euscelinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarawacus">
<emphasis box="[661,814,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">E. sarawacus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood, J. O." box="[822,1003,1611,1637]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580" refId="ref2284" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1882) Descriptions of new or imperfectly known species of Ichneumones Adsciti. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 25,17 - 48." type="book" year="1882">Westwood 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1020,1090,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,192,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1436,179,1898]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Euscelinus sarawacus Westwood, male, India. A. Habitus in lateral aspect; B. Head in frontal aspect; C. Wings; D. Antenna; E. Head and mesosoma in lateral aspect; F. Head and mesosoma in dorsal aspect; G. Propodeum and metasoma in dorsolateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816917/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), since no obvious differences are found (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[274,378,1647,1673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">syn. nov.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
